## THE PROOF SYSTEM: ONE PARAGRAPH

Classical mathematics proves by deduction from axioms.
This framework proves by **closure of independent routes**.

A result R is proven when ≥ 3 independent geometric paths arrive at R
with zero residual tension (ΔT=0). Independence means: the paths use
different subsets of the framework's building blocks. If one path has
an error, the others will disagree — the fracture is detectable.

This is not a new type of proof. It is the oldest verification method:
checking a calculation by an independent method. What is new is its
elevation to a primary geometric principle applicable to all claims
about number, space, and physical constants.

The claim "this is proven" in Opterium always means:
"multiple independent routes converge on the same address with ΔT=0."
It never means "this follows from an axiom we have not verified."

